---
import Page from "../layouts/Page.astro";
import CallToAction from "../components/CallToAction.astro";

const gh = "https://github.com/Formspec-org/formspec";
---

<Page
  title="About — Formspec"
  description="Who leads Formspec, why it exists, and what drives the project."
>
  <article class="about">

    <!-- ─── Header ─── -->
    <header class="about-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1>We kept solving the same problem. So we built the standard.</h1>
      <p class="about-lead">
        Formspec is led by
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-deeb/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Michael Deeb</a>,
        <a href="https://tealwolf.consulting/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TealWolf Consulting</a>, with
        <a href="https://focusconsulting.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Focus Consulting</a> as a strategic partner.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- ─── The Story ─── -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">The story</div>
      <h2>Years of building forms for government. Then we stopped and asked why.</h2>
      <p>
        We work with federal agencies and regulated industries — the kinds of organizations
        where a 200-field grant application or a clinical intake form isn't a side project,
        it's the primary interface between the institution and the people it serves.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every engagement started the same way: someone describes a complex form, a development
        team spends months building it, and then a requirements change means half of it gets
        rebuilt. The next client has different fields but the same structural problems —
        conditional logic, calculated budgets, cross-field validation, offline support, accessibility.
        We were solving the same category of problem from scratch every time.
      </p>
      <p>
        Web development has HTML. APIs have OpenAPI. Data interchange has JSON Schema.
        Forms — despite being everywhere in government, healthcare, and compliance — have nothing.
        No shared standard. Every organization builds from scratch or locks into a vendor platform.
      </p>
      <p>
        We decided to build the standard we wished existed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Who We Are ─── -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Who we are</div>
      <h2>Consultants who got tired of duct tape.</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-deeb/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Michael Deeb</a>
        leads the project through
        <a href="https://tealwolf.consulting/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TealWolf Consulting</a>, with
        <a href="https://focusconsulting.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Focus Consulting</a> as a strategic partner.
        The work comes from years of building and maintaining forms for grant programs,
        compliance reporting, and clinical workflows — and from the frustration of
        watching good teams spend months on problems that should have been solved once, well, for everyone.
      </p>
      <p>
        The project went from initial research to a working specification, dual reference implementations,
        a visual studio, and an MCP server in
        <a href="/blog/how-we-built-formspec/">about three weeks</a>.
        Not by cutting corners — by spending the first week entirely on getting the specification right,
        then letting the formality do the heavy lifting. When the boundaries are clean, the code writes fast.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Why Open Source ─── -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Why open source</div>
      <h2>A standard that only one company uses isn't a standard.</h2>
      <p>
        We built Formspec in the open because the problem it solves — a missing standard for complex
        forms — can't be solved by a single organization. Standards gain value through adoption.
        A form specification locked inside a proprietary platform is just a proprietary format with
        good marketing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Everything is <a href={`${gh}/blob/main/LICENSING.md`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">open-core licensed</a>.
        The specifications, the schemas, the implementations, the tooling. Form definitions are
        plain JSON files you own. No vendor dependency, no required runtime, no lock-in.
        We want people to build on this, fork it, write alternative implementations, and push
        it in directions we haven't thought of.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Get Involved ─── -->
    <section class="about-section about-section--last">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Get involved</div>
      <h2>Where to go from here.</h2>

      <div class="links-grid">
        <a href={gh} class="link-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="link-card-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="link-card-body">
            <h3>GitHub</h3>
            <p>Source code, specifications, schemas, and examples.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/" class="link-card">
          <div class="link-card-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M4 4h12v12H4z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M4 8h12M8 8v8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="link-card-body">
            <h3>Blog</h3>
            <p>Design decisions, deep dives, and how we built the project.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/features/" class="link-card">
          <div class="link-card-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="3" y="3" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <path d="M7 10l2 2 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="link-card-body">
            <h3>Features</h3>
            <p>What Formspec actually does — the capability breakdown.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/architecture/" class="link-card">
          <div class="link-card-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <circle cx="10" cy="5" r="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <circle cx="5" cy="15" r="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <circle cx="15" cy="15" r="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <path d="M10 7v3l-5 5M10 10l5 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="link-card-body">
            <h3>Architecture</h3>
            <p>How it's built — document model, packages, and dependency graph.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>

  <CallToAction />
</Page>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.5rem) 0;
  }

  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    max-width: 36rem;
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-lead a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .about-lead a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-section {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .about-section--last {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 52rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-section a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .about-section a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  /* ─── Links Grid ─── */

  .links-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .link-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.3s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .link-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent-dim);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .link-card-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--color-accent-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .link-card-body h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .link-card-body p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* ─── Mobile ─── */

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-header {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .about-section {
      padding: 2.5rem 0;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .about {
      padding-top: 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>
